id: pm-mcxr
title: "GH-206: test-all silent run process-liveness regression"
description: "Tracks GitHub issue #206: pm test-all can run silently and leave parent process alive after child activity."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-16T11:28:40.523Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-18T19:49:27.303Z"
author: codex-sdk-cli-consolidation-20260616
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Resolved GH-206 test-all liveness UX by preserving every stderr progress line in background workers and exposing current test-all item plus linked command state in compact background status.
expected_result: Background test-all runs provide visible current item/test-command progress and no stale non-runnable linked-test metadata remains on the item.
actual_result: "Background records include item_index, item_total, item_id, linked_test_index, linked_test_total, and current_command; temp tarball smoke passed with test-runs status and full coverage remained 100/100/100/100."
comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-18T12:21:55.941Z",codex-gpt5,"Partial implementation evidence: strict --fail-on-empty-test-run now marks zero-linked-test aggregate selections as failed with an explicit empty_run category and warning. Broader GH-206 liveness/progress work remains open intentionally."
  "2026-06-18T12:41:26.890Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up evidence: updated PRD test-all foreground contract to include fail_on_empty_test_run_triggered alongside the strict empty-run runtime result field."
  "2026-06-18T14:47:47.581Z",codex-gpt5,"Duplicate check before continuation: pm context/list/search found no in-progress items; canonical live lineages are pm-mcxr for GH-206 and pm-u8y9 for SDK.md resource-kind drift. No new pm item created."
  "2026-06-18T15:30:28.264Z",codex-gpt5,"Manual smoke evidence: packed @unbrained/pm-cli@2026.6.17 into a fresh temp project, installed from tarball with isolated PM_GLOBAL_PATH, ran pm init, created a task with a linked node command, ran pm test --run --progress successfully, ran pm test-all --status open --progress --fail-on-empty-test-run --json and observed ok=true linked_tests=1 passed=1, then pm validate --check-history-drift --json ok=true."
  "2026-06-18T15:31:02.483Z",codex-gpt5,"GitHub/observability evidence: gh pr list returned no open PRs; gh issues checked #206/#207 and open issue list; sentry issue list pm-cli --period 24h --query is:unresolved --fresh --json returned an empty data array; telemetry status showed enabled=true and last_successful_flush_at=2026-06-18T15:29:37.909Z; health --check-telemetry --summary --json returned ok=true."
  "2026-06-18T18:54:10.667Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation note: continuing GH-206 liveness UX on the existing item after duplicate check. Remaining scoped gap is background test-all progress parsing: foreground emits per-item progress, but the background record only structurally captures linked-test heartbeat fields."
  "2026-06-18T19:14:58.208Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence: implemented structured background test-all progress parsing for item_index/item_total/item_id plus current_command preservation, fixed stderr chunk handling to process every progress line, removed stale prose-only linked test metadata, and verified focused tests, linked pm tests, temp tarball smoke, build/static/contracts/changelog/validate, and full coverage 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-06-18T19:26:19.741Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up evidence: addressed Gemini/CodeRabbit stale progress-field feedback by clearing linked-test index/total/current_command/elapsed_ms when a test-all item progress line arrives; focused tests, build, static quality, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 passed after the fix."
  "2026-06-18T19:49:27.303Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up evidence: addressed remaining CodeRabbit/Gemini parser feedback by buffering partial stderr lines, ignoring non-progress stderr for structured progress updates, covering trailing no-newline progress, and simplifying item-progress phase handling. Focused test, static quality, and full coverage 100/100/100/100 passed."
